EALTH DISORDERS"}, {"i": 258, "t": "APPENDICES"}, {"i": 259, "t": "APPENDIX A"}, {"i": 260, "t": "MONITORING AND EXAMINATION STANDARDS"}, {"i": 261, "t": "This appendix on the use of psychotropic medications"}, {"i": 262, "t": "safety monitoring"}, {"i": 263, "t": "and psychiatric patients"}, {"i": 264, "t": "medical condition monitoring"}, {"i": 265, "t": "presents standard protocols for it."}, {"i": 266, "t": "A.1. Antipsikotik terapiyada metabolik monitorinq"}, {"i": 267, "t": "Atypical antipsychotics – especially olanzapine, quetiapine, clozapine –"}, {"i": 268, "t": "Metabolic syndrome increases the risk."}, {"i": 269, "t": "(weight gain, dyslipidemia, insulin resistance, diabetes)."}, {"i": 270, "t": "Monitoring chart (APA/ADA 2004, Illuminated ADA-APA-ACP-NAASO):"}, {"i": 271, "t": "Parametr"}, {"i": 272, "t": "Onset"}, {"i": 273, "t": "4 weeks"}, {"i": 274, "t": "8 weeks"}, {"i": 275, "t": "12 weeks"}, {"i": 276, "t": "Quarterly"}, {"i": 277, "t": "Annual"}, {"i": 278, "t": "Personal/Family history"}, {"i": 279, "t": "Weight, waist circumference"}, {"i": 280, "t": "Blood pressure"}, {"i": 281, "t": "Fasting glucose"}, {"i": 282, "t": "Fasting lipid profile"}, {"i": 283, "t": "✓ (every 2 years)"}, {"i": 284, "t": "If abnormality is detected:"}, {"i": 285, "t": "Weight gain ≥7%:"}, {"i": 286, "t": "consider medication switch (aripiprazole, ziprasidone—metabolically neutral);"}, {"i": 287, "t": "HbA1c ≥6.5% or fasting glucose ≥7:"}, {"i": 288, "t": "Diabetes Consultation"}, {"i": 289, "t": "LDL ≥3.4 mmol/L:"}, {"i": 290, "t": "Diet, statin."}, {"i": 291, "t": "Specific monitoring for clozapine (due to agranulocytosis):"}, {"i": 292, "t": "Duration"}, {"i": 293, "t": "Tezlik"}, {"i": 294, "t": "First 6 months"}, {"i": 295, "t": "Weekly WBC and absolute neutrophil count (ANC)"}, {"i": 296, "t": "7–12 ay"}, {"i": 297, "t": "Every 2 weeks"}, {"i": 298, "t": "12+ ay"}, {"i": 299, "t": "Monthly"}, {"i": 300, "t": "ANC indicators:"}, {"i": 301, "t": "≥2.0 × 10⁹/L"}, {"i": 302, "t": "Normal – continue treatment;"}, {"i": 303, "t": "weekly monitoring;"}, {"i": 304, "t": "Monitor every 2 days, hematology consultation;"}, {"i": 305, "t": "&lt;1,0:"}, {"i": 306, "t": "medication discontinued, hematologist intervention"}, {"i": 307, "t": "ECG monitoring with antipsychotics:"}, {"i": 308, "t": "QT interval prolongation risk:"}, {"i": 309, "t": "specifically ziprasidone, haloperidol IV, ondansetron combination;"}, {"i": 310, "t": "Baseline EKG"}, {"i": 311, "t": "in patients with risk factors (heart disease, electrolyte disturbance, >65 years);"}, {"i": 312, "t": "QTc >500 ms or >60 ms increase from baseline"}, {"i": 313, "t": "Medication change"}, {"i": 314, "t": "Medications increasing risk:"}, {"i": 315, "t": "chlorpromazine, haloperidol (high), thioridazine."}, {"i": 316, "t": "Hiperprolaktinemiya:"}, {"i": 317, "t": "Risperidon, amisulprid, paliperidon"}, {"i": 318, "t": "– high risk;"}, {"i": 319, "t": "Symptoms: amenorrhea, galactorrhea, sexual dysfunction, osteoporosis."}, {"i": 320, "t": "Basal prolactin; with recurrent symptom."}, {"i": 321, "t": "A.2. Litium monitorinqi"}, {"i": 322, "t": "Narrow therapeutic window"}, {"i": 323, "t": "level 0.6–1.2 mEq/L"}, {"i": 324, "t": ", &gt;1,5 toksik."}, {"i": 325, "t": "Parametr"}, {"i": 326, "t": "Onset"}, {"i": 327, "t": "Every 6 months"}, {"i": 328, "t": "Annual"}, {"i": 329, "t": "Lithium level"}, {"i": 330, "t": "Weekly for the 1st month, then every 6 months"}, {"i": 331, "t": "Kreatinin, eGFR"}, {"i": 332, "t": "TSH"}, {"i": 333, "t": "Electrolytes"}, {"i": 334, "t": "Kalsium"}, {"i": 335, "t": "EKG"}, {"i": 336, "t": "✓ (50+ years old)"}, {"i": 337, "t": "Pregnancy test"}, {"i": 338, "t": "Female of childbearing age"}, {"i": 339, "t": "Signs of lithium intoxication:"}, {"i": 340, "t": "Tremor (more severe);"}, {"i": 341, "t": "Tachycardia;"}, {"i": 342, "t": "Diarrhea, vomiting;"}, {"i": 343, "t": "Slow, confused speech;"}, {"i": 344, "t": "Ataxia;"}, {"i": 345, "t": "Convulsion – in severe conditions."}, {"i": 346, "t": "Check level in state change:"}, {"i": 347, "t": "dehydration, NSAID addition, ACE inhibitor addition, kidney function change."}, {"i": 348, "t": "A.3. Antikonvulsantlar (valproat, karbamazepin, lamotrigin)"}, {"i": 349, "t": "Valproat:"}, {"i": 350, "t": "Parametr"}, {"i": 351, "t": "Onset"}, {"i": 352, "t": "Every 6 months"}, {"i": 353, "t": "CBC (trombositopeniya)"}, {"i": 354, "t": "Liver function (AST, ALT)"}, {"i": 355, "t": "Valproate level"}, {"i": 356, "t": "With symptom or suspicion"}, {"i": 357, "t": "Monitoring signs of pancreatitis"}, {"i": 358, "t": "Every visit"}, {"i": 359, "t": "Pregnancy test"}, {"i": 360, "t": "ABSOLUTELY DEFINITE in elderly woman"}]